President Biden spoke with President Ghani of Afghanistan and discussed the situation in Afghanistan. They both reaffirmed their commitment to a bilateral partnership and President Biden emphasized continued U.S. support, including development and humanitarian aid for the Afghan people. They agreed that the Taliban's offensive goes against their claim to support a negotiated settlement. President Biden also reaffirmed the U.S.' commitment to supporting the Afghan security forces. They expressed concern about the loss of innocent lives, targeted killings, displacement of civilians, and damage to infrastructure. The U.S. has recently announced additional humanitarian and non-humanitarian assistance for Afghanistan. President Biden urged unity among Afghan leaders and emphasized continued U.S. diplomatic engagement for a political settlement.